which was 0.48. The lower 95% confidence interval exceeded 0.4 in all but two 
items, which was 0.39. This implied that the test-retest reliability of JOABPEQ 
was acceptable as a measure of outcome.
CONCLUSIONS: The tentative questionnaire of the JOABPEQ with 25 items was 
confirmed to be reliable enough to describe the quality of life of patients who 
suffer low back disorders.

